uage of Intuition\n|\nWith high hope and optimism, start swimming with time.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nAnd life is a good thing for a writer. It's where we get our raw material, for a start. We quite like to stop and watch it.\n\n- Neil\n|\nWhen you look into your soulmates eyes, you see the world; into your soulmates heart, you see the sky, and into your soulmates soul, you see the universe.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nOf course there is no formula for success, except perhaps an unconditional acceptance of life, and what it brings\n\n- Arthur\n|\nI wish I could fall asleep. But with a good book in my hands, I stay awake to finish reading.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nAppreciation and gratitude show your true wealth emotionally, spiritually and psychologically.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nHome isn't a place. Home is the people who love you most, the people who will always love you, forever and ever, no matter what.\n\n- Jennifer Lynn Barnes, All In\n|\nIf the radiance of a thousand suns were to burst at once into the sky, that would be like the splendor of the Mighty One... I am become Death, the Shatterer of Worlds.\n\n- The\n|\nWe've lost a lot of years, but you can't lose love. Not real love. It stays locked inside you, ready for whenever you are strong enough to find it again.\n\n- Martina Boone, Compulsion\n|\nWe are humiliated by what is powerful and mean, but awed by what is powerful and noble.\n\n- Alain de Botton, The Art of Travel\n|\nSow the seeds of love, kindness and peace.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nPainted desert, ocean of colorsun's worshiper, moon's loverpicture of a coyote's voicesandbox of angels, another toy.\n\n- Trine Daely, Life Games\n|\nIt's a helluva start, being able to recognize what makes you happy.\n\n- Lucille\n|\nPeace at home, peace in the world.\n\n- Mustafa\n|\nAs far as we can discern, the sole purpose of human existence is to kindle a light of meaning in the darkness of mere being.\n\n- C.G.\n|\nI may act like I don't care anymore, but if only you could see me inside, you'll know ho